caption: I stumbled across this place looking for lunch near my office (we just moved in a couple of months ago).  It had decent reviews, decided to check it out.  Walking in:  Very welcoming and warm was my first thought.  I had a garlic grilled cheese sandwich, tomato & onion salad and chocolate cake.  All three delicious - the grilled cheese was lightly toasted - perfection.  Day II,  grilled cheese again, caprese salad, pistachio cheesecake.   Grilled cheese was super garlicky - fantastic, salad - great - pistachio was excellent, but so rich could only finish 1/2.  Day III, 10" sausage pizza.  I ate everything (and I'm not a crust eater).  Not too greasy, great sausage coverage, cheesy.  I have to take a break from further discovery for a couple of weeks though. I'm putting on weight.  Paying is via your phone - which is nice and what I expect during Covid - and the food is served hot and quick.  The most I waited in my 3 day trial was maybe 5 minutes?  Never long enough for me to wonder what was going on.  Highly recommend.

I've had pizza here, which is really good. But the star of the show is their barbegue wings!  The meat is tender and falls off the bone (I hate tough wings). The sauce is perfect!  They have good desserts, and gourmet bottled soda. I love the root beer.
The pizza is really good...and the brownies are even better (lol)!!  I literally buy 5 at a time...they're that good!
Very nice place

This is some of the best Pizza I have ever had in D.C.! Now I will start by saying that they need to update their Menu on Yelp and their website to match some of the name changes and pricing. I was staying downtown during the 2021 Inauguration and open restaurants were becoming very hard to find. I was told of a local pizzeria that was still open during all the madness in D.C. by my hotel. The only thing was that you couldn't eat inside due to COVID and the inauguration security. The restaurant is only a few blocks away from the White House and some other major landmarks, and one block away from the hotel I was staying in. Once I found the place I walked in and it was incredibly clean. The chairs and tables were all push back against the wall due to the new rules right now, which was sad to me but everyone had a cheerful attitude when I walked in. Even though the streets were empty and intersections of the city was filled with soldiers the restaurant was still busy. People were calling in orders and picking them up. That was a great sign. I walked in and asked to look through their menu. I found that they had a wonderful list of things to eat, from Italian to chicken wings. The pizza was my main concern so I placed an order for the Meaty Boy, pepperoni, sausage, and bacon. Yum! After that I took a walk to their near by fridge and saw that they had some desserts, so I picked up a Tiramisu and for $6 not bad. The pizza was about $13 and about the size of a medium pizza, enough to fill up one person. I have to say that this place had great customer service during an amazing and scary time. It's almost like they didn't skip a beat. People got to eat, so why not pizza? The pizza was perfect. It had the right amount of cheese and sauce, it also came with sooooo much meat and the best part is that it wasn't greasy! The Tiramisu was soft and flavorful. I don't know how else to describe it, other than it was perfect. I was not expecting to have such a great dessert from a small pizzeria in D.C. but I did and I loved it. My dinner was so amazing that I only ate there my entire time in D.C., even if the other restaurants opened after the inauguration. So if you are visiting the White House, or you work in downtown D.C. and have never been to this place try it! You wont be sorry. It's just as good as or better than &Pizza. If I had to compare them to another pizza place. Enjoy!

Bozzelli’s Deli in Crystal City always goes above and beyond.  I am local to the Crystal City location and Bozzelli’s Deli has been keeping food on the table throughout this pandemic. The store is always exceptionally clean and organized. Every time I am picking up food the staff members are wearing personal protective masks and gloves. We ordered a Drunken Goat pizza, a personal favorite of mine.  The crust is both chewy and crisp and the ingredients taste fresh and farm-to-table.  My son is a picky eater and requested a pizza with no sauce.  The staff members were glad to oblige and made it exactly how he liked it.  The chicken cheese steak sandwich was delicious and such generous portions!  You really get a lot for your money.  That means a lot to me. Thanks, Bozzelli’s Deli for delicious quality food during these tough times!
